metadata.name: Maquette #95
metadata.description:
Like a photography of a city maquette with citizens.

Created in javascript / webGL using three.js and pathtracer.
May - June 2022
@arthurmchr

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî
Path tracing is an heavy GPU operation.
Depending on the device, it can takes a few seconds to render.

press P to pause / resume rendering (automatically paused after 100 rendering steps).

metadata.name: Merkki #21
metadata.description:
Merkki is an exploration of primitive forms, randomness and bold lines.
Drawing inspiration from mid-70s iconic single-color logotypes, this project revolves heavily around constraints and minimalism.

- 5 different shape types
- 3 grid sizes
- Mostly monochrome, with occasional color accents

Press ‚Äús‚Äù to save a 4000x4000px image.

metadata.name: Unicorn #9375
metadata.description:
All of us have dreams, and everyone would like to meet a fairy, a genie, a wizard, or someone else who will make our dreams come true in a snap of a finger or with the wave of a wand. But we're the only ones who can do it. We are those magical unicorns, unique, inimitable, with our own qualities and magical abilities.
These unicorns are the visualization of our inner selves that makes our dreams come true. An embodiment of all the best with a huge positive magical power.

metadata.name: Light reverberations #34
metadata.description:
‚ÄúThe tinnitus like silence tearing the eardrums; a glare of darkness burned into the retina. ‚Äú


As a visual & sound designer, my routine job is more related to new media installations, interactive programming design and lighting design. Explore to different luminaries and light sources, I gradually discover the relationship between light and sound waves. The role of reverberations are often sculptured the space when processing sounds, just like the lights play a similar role in 3D worlds. Reflections in the space make the sound more realistic, while the presence of light emphasis the dimensionality and depth of the space as well.

These scenes made of light and time remind me the painting and sculptures in the early 20th century, Futurism, which is characterized by technology, speed and violence. Umberto Boccioni and Gino Severini for instance. Nowadays, when we are free to deal with digital art beyond the existence of print or various archival forms, will it be an art movement called meta-futurism? Perhaps only things beyond our imagination can be called the future.

The project has been described during testing as being like picking up a camera that has fallen into space. It could be a collection of extreme brightness or endless darkness. If you decide to go into the space,  a carefully risk assessment is necessary.


Controls:

Click -> activate rotate control. (swipe gesture on mobile device)

Esc -> exit rotate and restart the rendering. (one tap on mobile device)

(Explore your own world by clicking on the canvas and rotate the viewpoint, tap ‚Äúesc‚Äù to see the new result.)

The code used to calculate path tracing environment is from the three.js-PathTracing-Renderer ([https://github.com/erichlof/THREE.js-PathTracing-Renderer](https://github.com/erichlof/THREE.js-PathTracing-Renderer)), created by Erich Loftis.

metadata.name: Bedlam #217
metadata.description:
Originally a study of paint brushes and texture, this project morphed. I started to find a medley of painting with the texture of handmade rugs, leveraging this medium to not just recreate the everyday, but let my imagination run. 

Enjoy each abstract piece that "Bedlam" has to offer, with 25 palettes, 5 brush styles, and an endless combination of stroke lengths and layering effects, there is much to be discovered.

It can take up to a minute for the Painting to finish, depending on your hardware.

Press 's' in Live View to save a png.

metadata.name: Haemo Globs #66
metadata.description:
The shape and function of haematids (red blood cells) has always fascinated me. Perhaps their mathematical smoothness and candy-like aspect resonated with me as a child. Their simple appearance distinguished them from the other cell types I had learned about. I imagined them engorged with sweet-flavoured oxygen and juicily popping under my bite.

I hope for this generative artwork to communicate my appreciation for these never-ending body travellers.
